{{Infobox United States federal proposed legislation | name = | fullname = To amend the Interstate Land Sales Full Disclosure Act to clarify how the Act applies to condominiums. | acronym = | nickname = | introduced in the = 113th | sponsored by = [[Carolyn Maloney|Rep. Carolyn B. Maloney (D, NY-12)]] | number of co-sponsors = 3 | public law url = | cite public law = {{USPL|113|167}} | cite statutes at large = | acts affected = [[Interstate Land Sales Full Disclosure Act]] | acts repealed = | title affected = | sections created = | sections affected = {{USCSub|15|1702}} | agenciesaffected = | authorizationsofappropriations = | appropriations = | leghisturl = | introducedin = House | introducedbill = {{USBill|113|hr|2600}} | introducedby = [[Carolyn Maloney|Rep. Carolyn B. Maloney (D, NY-12)]] | introduceddate = June 28, 2013 | committees = [[United States House Committee on Financial Services]], | passedbody1 = House of Representatives | passeddate1 = September 26, 2013 | passedvote1 = 410-0 | passedbody2 = Senate | passedas2 = | passeddate2 = September 18, 2014 | passedvote2 = [[Unanimous consent]] | conferencedate = | passedbody3 = | passeddate3 = | passedvote3 = | agreedbody3 = | agreeddate3 = | agreedvote3 = | agreedbody4 = | agreeddate4 = | agreedvote4 = | passedbody4 = | passeddate4 = | passedvote4 = | signedpresident = [[Barack Obama]] | signeddate = September 18, 2014 | unsignedpresident = | unsigneddate = | vetoedpresident = | vetoeddate = | overriddenbody1 = | overriddendate1 = | overriddenvote1 = | overriddenbody2 = | overriddendate2 = | overriddenvote2 = | amendments = | SCOTUS cases = }}
'''{{USPL|113|167}}''' (formerly the bill '''{{USBill|113|hr|2600}}'''), a United States public law, that is entitled "to amend the Interstate Land Sales Full Disclosure Act to clarify how the Act applies to condominiums," is a bill that was introduced into the [[United States House of Representatives]] during the [[113th United States Congress]]. The [[Interstate Land Sales Full Disclosure Act of 1968]] was passed in 1968 with the intention of helping protect consumers from land-related scams, but regulating the sale of land across state lines.<ref name=gwtol1>{{cite web|title=Interstate Land Sales Full Disclosure Act|url=http://greatwaytolearn.com/realestate/interstate-land-sales-full-disclosure-act/|publisher=greatwaytolearn.com|accessdate=23 September 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141011154322/http://greatwaytolearn.com/realestate/interstate-land-sales-full-disclosure-act/|archivedate=11 October 2014|df=}}</ref> The act requires sellers to prepare center information about the piece of property they are trying to sell and disclose it in a "Property Report." The law was originally administered by the [[United States Department of Housing and Urban Development]], but is currently run by the [[Consumer Financial Protection Bureau]]. H.R. 2600 would make changes to this law related to condominiums.
==Provisions of the bill== ''This summary is based largely on the summary provided by the [[Congressional Research Service]], a [[public domain]] source.''<ref name=2600sum>{{cite web|title=H.R. 2600 - Summary|url=http://beta.congress.gov/bill/113th/house-bill/2600|publisher=United States Congress|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref>
H.R. 2600 would amend the [[Interstate Land Sales Full Disclosure Act]] to exempt from certain registration and disclosure requirements the sale or lease of a [[condominium]] unit not already exempt from coverage under such Act.
==Procedural history== H.R. 2600 was introduced into the House on June 28, 2013 by [[Carolyn Maloney|Rep. Carolyn B. Maloney (D, NY-12)]].<ref name=2600allactions>{{cite web|title=H.R. 2600|url=http://beta.congress.gov/bill/113th-congress/house-bill/2600/all-actions/|publisher=United States Congress|accessdate=23 September 2013}}</ref> It was referred to the [[United States House Committee on Financial Services]].<ref name="2600allactions"/> On September 20, 2013, House Majority Leader [[Eric Cantor]] announced that H.R. 1961 would be on the legislative schedule for the week of September 23.<ref name=leadersschedule>{{cite web|title=Leader's Weekly Schedule - Week of September 23, 2013|url=http://majorityleader.gov/floor/9-23-13.pdf|publisher=House Majority Leader's Office|accessdate=23 September 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019171750/http://majorityleader.gov/floor/9-23-13.pdf|archivedate=19 October 2013|df=}}</ref> It was scheduled to be considered under a suspension of the rules on September 25, 2013.<ref name=peteSept20>{{cite news|last=Kasperowicz|first=Pete|title=A closer look at next week... Congress crashes on spending, debt ceiling|url=http://thehill.com/blogs/floor-action/house/323739-a-closer-look-at-next-week-congress-crashes-on-spending-debt-ceiling|accessdate=23 September 2013|newspaper=The Hill|date=20 September 2013}}</ref> On September 27, 2013, on the verge of a government shutdown by Republicans, the House of Representatives passed H.R. 2600 by a vote of 410-0.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.mondaq.com/unitedstates/x/269034/real+estate/On+The+Verge+Of+Government+Shutdown+US+House+Of+Reps+Unanimously+Votes+To+Amend |title=On The Verge Of Government Shutdown, US House Of Reps Unanimously Votes To Amend... |year=2013}}</ref> The bill would provide an exemption for condominiums from ILSA's registration requirements and would apply to all new constructions after enactment.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://maloney.house.gov/press-release/bipartisan-maloney-bill-clarifying-condominium-fraud-law-passes-house-410-0 |title= Bipartisan Maloney Bill Clarifying Condominium Fraud Law Passes House 410-0 |year= 2013 |deadurl= yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131020023337/http://maloney.house.gov/press-release/bipartisan-maloney-bill-clarifying-condominium-fraud-law-passes-house-410-0 |archivedate= 2013-10-20 |df= }}</ref> On September 18, 2014, the [[United States Senate]] voted to pass the bill with [[unanimous consent]]. On September 26, 2014, President [[Barack Obama]] signed the bill and it became {{USPL|113|167}}.<ref name="2600allactions"/>
==See also== *[[List of bills in the 113th United States Congress]] *[[Interstate Land Sales Full Disclosure Act of 1968]]
